Prior Plans shall be vested under this Plan at least to the extent that the interest of that Participant was vested under the Prior Plans as of the Effective Date. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">8.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">INCLUDED YEARS OF SERVICE &#150; VESTING </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For purposes of determining Years of Service under this Article, the
Plan shall take into account all Years of Service an Employee completes with a Participating Employer, including Years of Service as an Ineligible Employee. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">8.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FORFEITURES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan Administrator shall forfeit the non-vested portion of a terminated Participant&#146;s
Employer Contribution Account on the earliest of (a)&nbsp;the date of distribution of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance, or (b)&nbsp;the date the Participant has five consecutive Breaks in Service. For purposes of this section,
if the value of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance is zero, the Participant shall be deemed to have received a distribution of such Nonforfeitable Account balance as of the date of the Participant&#146;s termination of employment
with all Participating Employers. All forfeitures (including forfeitures made pursuant to Section&nbsp;14.5) shall be applied to pay administrative expenses of the Plan not otherwise paid pursuant to Section&nbsp;5.2, or to reduce employer
contributions to the Plan, including Matching, Company and Discretionary Contributions and restoration of forfeitures under Sections 8.6 and 14.5. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">8.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">RESTORATION OF FORFEITURES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a terminated Participant who has forfeited some portion of his or her account is
subsequently reemployed by a Participating Employer prior to the expiration of five consecutive Breaks in Service, the amount forfeited (without benefit of investment gains or losses) shall be restored if the Participant received a distribution of
Plan benefits on account of termination of participation in the Plan and the Participant repays to the Trust Fund the full dollar amount distributed on account of the termination within five years of the reemployment date. Any such amounts shall be
restored to the account of the reemployed Participant as of the last day of the Plan Year in which the repayment was made. The restoration shall be made from any forfeitures available. If no forfeitures are available, a Participating Employer shall
make a special contribution for this purpose. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Article 9 Distribution of Benefits </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION AFTER AGE 59<SUP STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB> OR UPON TOTAL DISABILITY </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may apply for a distribution of all or a portion of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance at any time after attaining age 59<SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB> or upon reaching Total Disability. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 27</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION AFTER SEVERANCE FROM EMPLOYMENT </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may apply for a distribution of the total of the
Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance at any time after severance of employment with all Participating Employers for any reason. Subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(a), a Participant may, instead, delay distribution until distribution is
required under Section&nbsp;9.6(a). </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FORM OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The normal form of benefit shall be a single-sum distribution of the Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance, which shall be made to the Participant, if living, or if not, to the Participant&#146;s surviving Spouse, but if there is no surviving Spouse or if the Spouse has consented in a manner conforming to Section&nbsp;13.1,
then to the Participant&#146;s designated Beneficiary. The distribution shall be made as a lump-sum payment in cash, with the exception of the portion of an account invested in Employer Stock, with respect to which the Participant may elect a
distribution in kind. There shall be no installment form of distribution except as provided under Section&nbsp;9.6 with respect to required minimum distributions. Any partial distribution permitted or required under the Plan shall be made on a
pro-rata basis from all of the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts and investment funds, except that required minimum distributions shall be made from a Participant&#146;s Roth Elective Deferral Account only after complete distribution from all
other accounts and correction of excess Annual Additions shall be made in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.4. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LATEST DATE FOR COMMENCEMENT OF BENEFITS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Under the Act, distribution of the Participant&#146;s vested Account
shall begin no later than the 60<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> day after the latest of the following: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The close of the Plan Year in which the Participant attains age 65 or Normal Retirement Age, if earlier; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The close of the Plan Year in which occurs the 10<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> anniversary of the year in which the Participant commenced participation in the Plan; or </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The close of the Plan Year in which the Participant terminates Service with all Participating Employers. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Notwithstanding the foregoing, the failure of a Participant to elect a distribution shall be deemed to be an election to defer commencement of distribution of
any benefit sufficient to satisfy this section. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DEATH DISTRIBUTION PROVISIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If the Participant dies before distribution of the Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance has been made, the Participant&#146;s Beneficiary may apply for a distribution of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance in a single sum. Subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(a), the Beneficiary may, instead,
delay distribution until distribution is required under Section&nbsp;9.6(b). </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.6</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">MINIMUM DISTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Before Death</U>. Notwithstanding any other provision in this Plan, the entire interest of each Participant shall be distributed not later than as follows: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">to the Participant not later than the Required Beginning Date, as defined in Section&nbsp;9.6(c), or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">beginning not later than the Required Beginning Date, in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Secretary under Code &#167; 401(a)(9), </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(i)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">over the life of such Participant or over the lives of such Participant and his or her designated Beneficiary, or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(ii)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">over a period not extending beyond the life expectancy of such Participant or the life expectancy of such Participant and his or her designated Beneficiary. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participant&#146;s Spouse is not his or her designated Beneficiary, a method of payment to the Participant may not provide more than incidental benefits to the Beneficiary pursuant to the minimum distribution
incidental benefit requirement in the Treasury Regulations issued under Code &#167; 401(a)(9). </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 28</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Participants who are not 5% owners and who have not terminated service with all Participating Employers but who were receiving minimum distributions under prior law may elect to discontinue such distributions.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>After Death</U>. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this Plan, the entire interest of each Participant shall be distributed not later than as follows: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participant&#146;s death occurs after his or her Required Beginning Date, the remaining portion of the Participant&#146;s interest shall be distributed to the Participant&#146;s Beneficiary, in accordance with
regulations prescribed by the Secretary under Code &#167; 401(a)(9), at least as rapidly as under the method of distributions to the Participant being used under Section&nbsp;9.3 or 9.6(a) as of the date of the Participant&#146;s death. For this
purpose, the Participant&#146;s entire remaining interest may be distributed to the Beneficiary in a single lump sum not later than the date that payment to the Beneficiary is required to commence under Code &#167; 401(a)(9). </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participant&#146;s death occurs prior to his or her Required Beginning Date, distribution shall be made to the Participant&#146;s Beneficiary as a lump sum no later than the end of the calendar year containing
the fifth anniversary of the Participant&#146;s death. If the Participant&#146;s designated Beneficiary is the Participant&#146;s Spouse, and if the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance (as determined under Section&nbsp;9.11(a)) exceeds
$5,000, then, notwithstanding the above, the Spouse may elect, in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Secretary under Code &#167; 401(a)(9), to receive distribution of the Participant&#146;s entire interest over a period not exceeding the
Spouse&#146;s life expectancy, provided that distribution to the Spouse commences no later than December&nbsp;31 of the calendar year in which the Participant would have attained age 70<SUP STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB
STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB> or, if later, December&nbsp;31 of the calendar year immediately following the calendar year in which the employee died. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Required Beginning Date</U>. For a Participant who is a 5% owner, a Participant&#146;s Required Beginning Date is the April&nbsp;1 following the calendar year in which the Participant attains age 70<SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB>. For a Participant who is not a 5% owner, a Participant&#146;s Required Beginning Date is the April&nbsp;1 following the later of the calendar year in which
the Participant attains age 70<SUP STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB> or the calendar year in which the Participant terminates employment with all Participating Employers. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>General</U>. Notwithstanding any other provision in the Plan to the contrary, all distributions will be made in accordance with Code Section&nbsp;401(a)(9) and the regulations thereunder. Minimum required
distributions under Code Section&nbsp;401(a)(9) are made first from a Participant&#146;s non-Roth accounts (pro rata) and next from a Participant&#146;s Roth accounts (pro rata). </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION UNDER QUALIFIED DOMESTIC RELATIONS ORDER </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Distribution of all or a portion of a Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance will be made according to the terms of a &#147;qualified domestic relations order&#148; to the spouse, former spouse, child or other dependent of a Participant, even though the Participant is not otherwise eligible for
a distribution under the Plan. A qualified domestic relations order is a domestic relations order, judgment, or decree (including the approval of a property settlement agreement) that (a)&nbsp;relates to the provision of child support, alimony, or
property rights to a spouse, former spouse, child, or other dependent of a Participant and (b)&nbsp;is made pursuant to the domestic relations law of any state; provided that the Plan Administrator determines that such order meets the requirements
of Code Section&nbsp;414(p) and the Plan&#146;s Procedures for Processing Domestic Relations Orders (&#147;QDRO Procedures&#148;). Reasonable legal fees and expenses incurred in determining if an order is a qualified domestic relations order, shall
be charged to the account of the Participant and the account of the alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) seeking the determination, as provided in the QDRO Procedures. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">An alternate payee may apply for a distribution of the portion of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance that is payable to the alternate payee
pursuant to the qualified domestic relations order any time after the order is determined to be a qualified domestic relations order. Subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(a), the alternate payee may, instead, delay distribution until the alternate payee
attains age 65, at which time distribution shall be made to the alternate payee. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 29</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.8</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">HARDSHIP DISTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A current Employee who is also a Participant may request a distribution of funds from
the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account in the event of certain financial hardships, if the distribution meets the requirements of this section and the deemed hardship distribution standards of Treasury Regulation 1.401(k)-1(d)(3) (as
modified by subsequent laws). The amount of a hardship distribution shall not exceed Salary Deferral Contributions (excluding amounts received as a loan), excluding earnings. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must satisfy the deemed immediate and heavy financial need requirements of Treasury Regulations, which at present constitute the following financial needs: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expenses for (or necessary to obtain) medical care that would be deductible under Code Section&nbsp;213(d) (determined without regard to whether the expenses exceed 7.5% of adjusted gross income); </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Costs directly related to the purchase of a principal residence for the Participant (excluding mortgage payments); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payment of tuition, related educational fees, and room and board expenses, for up to the next 12 months of post-secondary education for the Participant, or the Participant&#146;s spouse, children, or dependents (as
defined in Code Section&nbsp;152 without regard to Section&nbsp;152(b)(1), (b)(2) and (d)(1)(B)); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payments necessary to prevent the eviction of the Participant from the Participant&#146;s principal residence or foreclosure on the mortgage on that residence. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payments for burial or funeral expenses for the Participant&#146;s deceased parent, spouse, children or dependents (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;152 without regard to Code Section&nbsp;152(d)(1)(B)); or
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(6)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expenses for the repair of damage to the Participant&#146;s principal residence that would qualify for the casualty deduction determined under Code Section&nbsp;165 (determined without regard to whether the loss exceeds
10% of adjusted gross income). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must be deemed necessary to satisfy an immediate and heavy financial need of the Participant under Treasury Regulations. Those Treasury Regulations at present require: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant has obtained all other currently available distributions (including distributions of ESOP dividends under Code Section&nbsp;404(k), but not hardship distributions), and nontaxable (at the time of the
loan) loans, under this Plan and all other plans maintained by Participating Employers; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant may make no further Salary Deferral Contributions (or any other employee contributions) to this Plan or to any other plans maintained by Participating Employers for a period of 6 months from the date the
hardship distribution is posted to the Participant&#146;s Account by the Trustee (the &#147;suspension period&#148;). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For
purposes of this Section&nbsp;8.2(b), the phrase &#147;plans maintained by Participating Employers&#148; means all qualified and non-qualified plans of deferred compensation maintained by Participating Employers. However, the phrase does not include
contributions to health or welfare benefit plans including health and welfare plans that are part of a cafeteria plan within the meaning of Code Section&nbsp;125. In addition, for purposes of Section&nbsp;8.2(b)(2), the phrase also includes a stock
option, stock purchase, or similar plan maintained by a Participating Employer. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must not be in excess of the amount of the immediate and heavy financial need of the Participant. The amount of an immediate and heavy financial need may include any amounts necessary to pay any
federal, state, or local income taxes or penalties reasonably anticipated to result from the distribution. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 30</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">A Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Contributions to the Plan (other than Catch-Up Contributions) shall automatically resume effective the first day of the first pay period (or extended pay period as provided in
Section&nbsp;1.62(a)) ending at least 30 days following the end of the suspension period described in paragraph (b)(2), above, based on the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement last in effect prior to the suspension period. However, the
preceding sentence shall not apply to a Participant who, within 30 days following the end of the suspension period and in the manner required by the Plan Administrator, submits a Salary Deferral Agreement electing a different or no Compensation
reduction percentage. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.9</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DIRECT ROLLOVER FOR ELIGIBLE DISTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A distributee may elect, at the time and in the manner prescribed
by the Administrator, to have any portion of an eligible rollover distribution paid directly to an eligible retirement plan specified by the distributee in a direct rollover. However, a direct rollover of a distribution from a Roth Elective Deferral
Account will only be made to another Roth elective deferral account under an applicable retirement plan described in Code Section&nbsp;402A(e)(1) or to a Roth IRA described in Code Section&nbsp;408A. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following definitions shall apply to the foregoing: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Eligible rollover distribution</U>: An eligible rollover distribution is any distribution of all or any portion of the balance to the credit of the distributee, except that an eligible rollover distribution does not
include: any distribution that is one of a series of substantially equal periodic payments (not less frequently than annually) made for the life (or life expectancy) of the distributee or the joint lives (or joint life expectancies) of the
distributee and the distributee&#146;s designated beneficiary, or for a specified period of ten years or more; any distribution to the extent such distribution is required under Section&nbsp;401(a)(9) of the Code; any distribution made on account of
hardship; and amounts that are not includable in gross income (&#147;after-tax amounts&#148;). Notwithstanding the foregoing, a portion of a distribution shall not fail to be an eligible rollover distribution merely because the portion consists of
after-tax amounts, provided such portion may be transferred only to an individual retirement account or annuity described in Section&nbsp;408(a) or (b)&nbsp;of the Code, or in a direct rollover to a qualified trust or to an annuity contract
described in Section&nbsp;403(b) of the Code and such trust or contract provides for separate accounting for amounts so transferred (and earnings thereon), including separate accounting for the portion of such distribution which is includible in
gross income and the portion of such distribution which is not so includible. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Eligible retirement plan</U>: An eligible retirement plan is an individual retirement account described in Code Section&nbsp;408(a), an individual retirement annuity described in Code Section&nbsp;408(b), an annuity
plan described in Code Section&nbsp;403(a), an annuity contract under Code Section&nbsp;403(b) and an eligible Code Section&nbsp;457(b) deferred compensation plan maintained by a state, political subdivision of a state, or any agency or
instrumentality of a state or political subdivision of a state, as long as the accepting account or plan agrees to separately account for amounts transferred from this Plan, or a qualified trust described in Code Section&nbsp;401(a), that accepts
the distributee&#146;s eligible rollover distribution. An eligible retirement plan also includes a Roth IRA, as defined in Code Section&nbsp;408A. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Distributee</U>: A distributee includes an Employee or former Employee. In addition, the Employee&#146;s or former Employee&#146;s surviving Spouse and the Employee&#146;s or former Employee&#146;s Spouse or former
Spouse who is the alternate payee under a qualified domestic relations order, as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p), are distributees with regard to the interest of the Spouse or former Spouse. A distributee also includes the Employee&#146;s or
former Employee&#146;s non-Spouse Beneficiary with regard to the interest of the non-Spouse Beneficiary. In the case of a non-Spouse Beneficiary, the direct rollover may be made only to (i)&nbsp;an individual retirement account or annuity described
in Code Sections 408(a) or (b)&nbsp;(&#147;IRA&#148;), or (ii)&nbsp;a Roth IRA as described in Code Section&nbsp;408A, provided such IRA or Roth IRA is established on behalf of the Beneficiary and will be treated as an inherited IRA or Roth IRA
pursuant to Code Section&nbsp;402(c)(11). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Direct rollover</U>: A direct rollover is a payment by the plan to the eligible retirement plan specified by the distributee. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 31</TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.10</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">AMOUNT AND TIMING OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The amount of a distribution to a Participant, Beneficiary, or alternate
payee shall not exceed the value of such individual&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance on the distribution date, reduced for outstanding loans, administrative expenses, and other appropriate amounts. Distribution shall be made within an
administratively practicable period after the individual&#146;s application therefor (or the date benefits become distributable without the individual&#146;s consent) and after the Plan Administrator receives all documents or information required to
confirm the distribution is proper under the law and the terms of the Plan. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.11</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">NOTICE AND CONSENT TO DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Small Benefit Distribution Without Consent</U>: If the value of a Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance does not exceed $5,000 (determined without regard to the Participant&#146;s Employee Contribution
Account) and the Participant has severed employment with all Participating Employers, distribution shall be made to the Participant without the Participant&#146;s consent, subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(d). Distribution shall also be made to a
Beneficiary or alternate payee without that individual&#146;s consent if the value of that individual&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance does not exceed $5,000 (determined without regard to the Employee Contribution Account). </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Participant and Alternate Payee Notice and Consent Requirements</U>: Distribution shall not be made to a Participant (or alternate payee) before Normal Retirement Age without the Participant&#146;s (or alternate
payee&#146;s) consent if the Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) Nonforfeitable Account Balance exceeds $5,000 (determined without regard to the Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) Employee Contribution Account). No less than
30 days and no more than 180 days before the date of a distribution for which a Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) consent is required under this section, the Plan Administrator shall provide the Participant (or alternate payee) with the
notice described in Treasury Regulation &#167; 1.411(a)-11(c) or, in accordance with Treasury Regulations, a summary of that notice. In addition to describing a Participant&#146;s right (if any) to defer receipt of a distribution, such notice shall
also describe the consequences of failing to defer receipt of a distribution. Notwithstanding the above, distribution may be made less than 30 days after such notice or summary is given, provided that: (1)&nbsp;the Plan Administrator clearly informs
the Participant (or alternate payee) that the Participant (or alternate payee) has a right to a period of at least 30 days after receiving the notice or summary to consider the decision of whether or not to elect a distribution, and (2)&nbsp;the
Participant (or alternate payee), after receiving the notice or summary, affirmatively elects a distribution. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Rollover Notice</U>: No less than 30 days and no more than 180 days before the date of a distribution that is an eligible rollover distribution (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9), the Plan Administrator shall provide
the distributee (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9) of such distribution with the notice described in Section&nbsp;402(f) of the Code or, in accordance with Treasury Regulations, a summary of that notice. Notwithstanding the above, distribution may be
made less than 30 days after such notice or summary is given, provided that: (1)&nbsp;the Plan Administrator clearly informs the distributee that the distributee has a right to a period of at least 30 days after receiving the notice or summary to
consider the decision of whether or not to elect a direct rollover, and (2)&nbsp;the distributee, after receiving the notice or summary, affirmatively elects a distribution. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Automatic Rollovers</U>: In the event of a mandatory distribution to a Participant greater than $1,000 in accordance with the provisions of Section&nbsp;9.11(a), if the Participant does not elect to have such
distribution paid directly to an eligible retirement plan specified by the Participant in a direct rollover or to receive the distribution directly, then the Plan Administrator shall pay the distribution in a direct rollover to an individual
retirement plan designated by the Plan Administrator. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.12</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">USE OF ELECTRONIC MEDIUM </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Medium for Notices</U>: The Plan Administrator may provide a Participant, Beneficiary, or alternate payee with the notices (or summaries of the notices) described in Section&nbsp;9.11(b) and (c)&nbsp;of the Plan and
Section&nbsp;3405 of the Code either on a written paper document or through an electronic medium that is reasonably accessible to the recipient and that is provided under a system that satisfies the requirements of applicable Treasury Regulations.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 32</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Medium for Application, Consent and Direct Rollover Election</U>: The Plan Administrator may permit a Participant, Beneficiary, or alternate payee to apply for and consent to a distribution and to elect whether or
not to make a direct rollover either on a written paper document or through an electronic medium that is reasonably accessible to the individual and that is provided under a system that satisfies the requirements of Treasury Regulation &#167;
1.411(a)-11(f)(2) to the extent applicable. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Article 10 Loans to Participants </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOAN PROGRAM </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may borrow limited amounts from the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account
(excluding his or her Roth Elective Deferral Account), Matching Contribution Account (to the extent vested), Profit Sharing Contribution Account, any Nondeductible Voluntary Contribution Account established under a Prior Plan, and any Rollover
Account established under Section&nbsp;6.1 (referred to collectively in this Article as &#147;eligible accounts&#148;). Participant loans shall not be made from a Participant&#146;s Company or Discretionary Contribution Accounts, ESOP Dividend
Reinvestment Account, Rescission Account, Qualified Non-Elective Contribution Account, Roth Elective Deferral Account, or from the non-vested portion of the Participant&#146;s Matching Contribution Account. Only one loan from the plan may be
outstanding at any time, and outstanding loans may not be amended or refinanced. Moreover, a Participant who has an outstanding loan from any other plan of a Participating Employer is not eligible for a loan from this Plan until the loan to the
other plan is repaid in full. In the event of default on a plan loan, a Participant may not apply for another loan earlier than six months after the defaulted loan is repaid in full. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee may make a loan to a Participant from the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts, in accordance with the terms of this Article and any written loan
policy, upon the application of a Participant who is in Eligible Employment and who meets objective criteria established in loan documents to ensure that the loan will be repaid according to its terms. The loan program shall be administered in a
uniform and nondiscriminatory manner in accordance with established rules and procedures, which may be changed from time to time. The Plan Administrator may establish a written loan policy separate from this document, and any such policy, as amended
from time to time, is incorporated herein by this reference. Loans shall be made on a reasonably equivalent basis and shall be available without regard to a Participant&#146;s race, color, religion, gender, age, or national origin. Furthermore,
loans shall not be made available to Highly Compensated Employees in an amount greater than the amount made available to other Participants. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">AMOUNT OF LOAN </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant loan shall not be granted for less than $1000, and the maximum amount of a loan
(when added to the outstanding balance of all other loans from all qualified plans of Participating Employers after application of the employer aggregation rules of Code Section&nbsp;414(b), (c)&nbsp;and (m)) shall not exceed $50,000, reduced by the
highest outstanding balance of all such loans during the one year period ending on the day before the day on which the loan is made <I>minus</I> the outstanding balance of all loans from the plan on the date on which the loan is made. In addition,
no loan shall exceed the amount that is 45% of the fair market value of the vested portion of a Participant&#146;s aggregate account balance (excluding accumulated deductible employee contributions as defined in Code Section&nbsp;72(p)(5)(B), if
any) at the time the loan is requested and 50% of such amount at the time the loan is made. Furthermore, a Participant loan shall not be granted in an amount that would require loan payments that exceed 25% of the Participant&#146;s normal bi-weekly
pay that is available for payroll deduction for repayment of the loan. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">TERM OF LOAN </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Participant loans shall provide for repayment within four years, except that a Participant may
request a repayment period of up to 15 years if the purpose of the loan is to acquire a dwelling unit that is to be used as the principal residence of the Participant within a reasonable period of time, determined at the time the loan is made. The
determination of whether a loan qualifies for the longer repayment period shall be made in accordance with regulations established under Code Section&nbsp;72(p)(2)(B)(ii), as amended from time to time. Under current regulations, &#147;principal
residence&#148; has the same meaning as under Code Section&nbsp;121, and the tracing rules of Code Section&nbsp;163(h)(3)(B) shall be used in determining whether a loan is used for the acquisition of such a residence. However, loans requested after
the date a principal residence is acquired do not qualify for the longer repayment period. Also, loans for the purpose of remodeling a current residence or for refinancing do not qualify for the longer repayment period. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 33</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">INTEREST RATE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Participant loans shall bear a reasonable rate of interest, determined quarterly by the Plan
Administrator or its designated agent. The rate of interest shall be the rate in effect at the time the Trustee issues the loan documents, so long as the Participant completes and returns the documents to the Trustee within 30 days of the issue
date. The interest rate shall comply with the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act to the extent it is applicable to a Participant&#146;s loan. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOAN ORIGINATION FEE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee may charge a reasonable loan origination fee, which shall be deducted from
the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts at the time the loan is made. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.6</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">REPAYMENT SCHEDULE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">All loans shall provide for level amortization over the term of the loan and shall require
repayment through payroll deduction on a bi-weekly basis. If a Participant refuses to authorize payroll deductions for repayment of the loan, the loan shall not be made. If in any pay period pay is insufficient to cover the entire payment due or if
payroll deductions are discontinued for any reason, payment must be remitted to the Trustee directly by the Participant on the same bi-weekly basis. A Participant may prepay the entire outstanding balance of a loan, including accrued interest,
without penalty at any time but may not make partial pre-payments. Upon termination of employment, a loan shall become due and payable within 30 days of the date of the termination, regardless of whether or not the Participant seeks a distribution
from the Plan, and shall be in default and offset as provided in Section&nbsp;10.12 if not paid in full within 30 days of the date of termination. If a Participant dies while a loan is outstanding, the loan shall be in default and offset as provided
in Section&nbsp;10.12. Loan repayments will not be suspended under Code Section&nbsp;414(u). </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">SECURITY </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In order to secure repayment of the loan, a Participant seeking a loan from the Plan must grant the
Trustee a security interest in 50% of the Participant&#146;s aggregate vested account balance at the time of the loan. At the time of any distribution to a Participant who has terminated employment with all Participating Employers or to a
Beneficiary after the death of a Participant, the amount of the actual cash distribution shall be reduced by the outstanding balance of any loan to the Participant, to the extent of the Trustee&#146;s security interest in the Participant&#146;s
accounts, and the distribution shall be reported as a distribution of the actual cash amount plus the loan offset amount, in accordance with applicable law. In the event a Participant&#146;s loan is in default, the Trustee shall make a distribution
in the form of a loan offset in accordance with Section&nbsp;10.12. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.8</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOAN APPLICATION AND DOCUMENTATION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant who wishes to take a loan from his or her eligible accounts
shall complete the application required by the Plan. The application shall be reviewed by an agent designated by the Plan Administrator to review loan applications, and the agent shall determine whether or not the Participant meets the objective
criteria specified herein and in policies, standards, criteria, and forms applicable to the Plan. If the agent approves a loan application, the Trustee shall be instructed to make the loan upon receipt of a legally binding promissory note and
security agreement properly executed by the Participant. The Plan Administrator may permit Participants to apply for loans and to enter into loan agreements, including promissory notes, security agreements and salary reduction agreements, in an
electronic medium that is reasonably accessible to Participants and that is provided under a system that satisfies the requirements of Treasury Regulation &#167; 1.72(p) &#150; 3(b)(2). Such agreements shall be legally binding and enforceable to the
same extent as agreements in writing and shall be deemed to be in writing and signed by the Participant for any and all purposes. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.9</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">SOURCE OF LOAN </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A loan that is approved by the Plan Administrator or its agent shall be made on a pro-rata
basis from all of the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts and investment funds. Repayment of such loans shall be made pro-rata back to such accounts and shall be invested as other funds in the accounts at the time the repayment is made. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.10</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOANS IN ARREARS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a loan payment is not made within 30 days of the time it is due, the loan payment shall be
considered in arrears. The Trustee shall inform the Plan Administrator or its designated agent promptly of any loan payment that is in arrears, and the Plan Administrator or its designated agent shall press the Participant for repayment. When a
</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 34</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">
Participant whose loan payment is in arrears (but is not yet in default) returns to active employment, payroll deductions to repay the loan shall recommence immediately, and multiple payroll
deductions may be taken or the Plan Administrator may take other action as permitted by law to bring the loan current. If the applicable loan agreement and promissory note do not provide otherwise, a Participant may elect either reamortization or
multiple payroll deductions, or both, in order to bring the loan current. If the Participant does not make a timely election of the method to be used to bring the loan current, the Plan Administrator or its designated agent may institute any and all
collection methods allowed by the loan agreement, promissory note, and applicable law. For loans made on or after January&nbsp;1, 2004, loans will be considered in arrears when a loan payment is not made when due. Further, in order to bring a loan
in arrears current, a Participant must make the missed payment. Reamortization will not be allowed as a way to bring a loan in arrears current. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.11</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DEEMED DISTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Subject to Section&nbsp;10.12, the Trustee shall report a Participant loan with a loan
payment in arrears as a &#147;deemed distribution&#148; for income tax purposes when the loan is in default, as required by Code Section&nbsp;72(p) and regulations thereunder. A loan is in default and is a deemed distribution under Code
Section&nbsp;72(p) when a missed payment is not made by the end of the applicable cure period. For loans made prior to January&nbsp;1, 2004, the cure period extends to the last day of the calendar quarter following the calendar quarter in which the
loan <SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"></SUP>payment in arrears was due. For loans made on or after January&nbsp;1, 2004, the cure period extends to the 90<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> day following the date
the loan payment was due. For loans made after 2001, the cure period for purposes of a deemed distribution shall not be further extended due to an Approved Absence. In the event that a deemed distribution is required, the Trustee shall report as the
deemed distribution the entire outstanding balance of the loan, including accrued interest, at the time of the deemed distribution. A deemed distribution shall be treated as an actual distribution for all purposes under Code &#167; 72 and Plan
provisions implementing Code &#167; 72. Not withstanding the above, a loan that is deemed distributed (including interest accruing thereafter) and that has not been actually repaid (such as by offset) is considered outstanding for purposes of
determining the maximum permissible amount of a subsequent loan under Section&nbsp;10.2. Payroll deductions to repay a loan shall not be required after a loan has been deemed distributed. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.12</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">PARTICIPANT LOAN OFFSET </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a Participant Loan is in default, the Trustee will reduce the Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance and report the loan as a loan offset in accordance with the terms of the security agreement for the loan if (1)&nbsp;the Participant attains or has attained age 59<SUP STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB
STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB>, (2)&nbsp;the Participant has severed his or her employment from all Participating Employers, (3)&nbsp;the Participant has reached Total Disability, or (4)&nbsp;the Participant has died. The date of the offset
will be the date the loan was first in default and deemed distributed, or, if later, the date on which the Participant attained age 59<SUP STYLE="vertical-align:top">&nbsp;1</SUP>&#8260;<SUB STYLE="vertical-align:bottom">2</SUB>, severed employment,
reached Total Disability, or died. In the case of a loan in default that has previously been reported as a deemed distribution, the Trustee shall report an offset in a manner that does not cause the Participant to suffer tax liability twice. A loan
offset shall be treated as an actual distribution for all purposes under the Plan and the Code and as a repayment in full of the Participant&#146;s loan that is in default. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Article 11 Rights and Remedies of Participants </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">11.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">QUARTERLY STATEMENTS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Each Plan Year quarter, the Plan Administrator shall deliver to each Participant (and to
any Beneficiary of a deceased Participant) a written statement that meets the applicable requirements of ERISA Section&nbsp;105(a). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In addition, within
the time prescribed by law, the Plan Administrator shall furnish to Participants a summary of the annual report filed by the Plan Administrator with the United States Department of Labor. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">No Participant, except a member of the Committee, shall have the right to inspect the records reflecting the Account of any other Participant. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">11.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">ASSIGNMENT OR ALIENATION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Except with respect to federal income tax withholding and with respect to participant
loans described in Article X hereof, neither a Participant nor a Beneficiary shall assign or alienate any benefit provided under the Plan, and the Trustee shall not recognize any such assignment or alienation. The preceding sentence shall not apply
to the creation, assignment, or recognition of a right to any benefit payable with respect to a Participant pursuant to a </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 35</TD></TR></TABLE>
