 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">
as of the later of the date the Employer adopts the amendment, or the date the amendment becomes effective) shall not be less than the Nonforfeitable percentage of that Account balance computed
under the Plan without regard to the amendment. Except as permitted by law, no amendment to the Plan shall decrease a Participant&#146;s Account balance or eliminate an optional form of distribution. If the Employer makes a permissible amendment to
the Vesting Schedule, each Participant having at least three Years of Service with a Participating Employer may irrevocably elect to have the percentage of his Nonforfeitable Account balance computed under the Plan without regard to the amendment.
The Participant must file his election with the Plan Administrator within 60 days of the latest of (a)&nbsp;the Employer&#146;s adoption of the amendment; (b)&nbsp;the effective date of the amendment; or (c)&nbsp;the Participant&#146;s receipt of a
copy of the amendment. The Plan Administrator, as soon as practicable, shall forward a true copy of any amendment to the Vesting Schedule to each affected Participant, together with an explanation of the effect of the amendment, the appropriate form
upon which the Participant may make an election to remain under the Vesting Schedule provided under the Plan prior to the amendment, and notice of the time within which the Participant must make an election to remain under the prior Vesting
Schedule. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">15.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISCONTINUANCE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Employer shall have the right, at any time, to suspend or discontinue its contributions
under the Plan, and to terminate this Plan and the Trust. The Plan shall terminate upon the first to occur of the following: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The date terminated by action of the Employer or the Committee, acting in a plan sponsor capacity; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The date the Employer shall be judicially declared bankrupt or insolvent; or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The dissolution, merger, consolidation, or reorganization of the Employer or the sale by the Employer of all or substantially all of its assets, unless the successor or purchaser makes provision to continue the Plan, in
which event the successor or purchaser shall substitute itself as the Employer under this Plan. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">15.6</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FULL VESTING ON TERMINATION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Notwithstanding any other provision of this Plan to the contrary, upon the date of
either full or partial termination of the Plan, or, if applicable, upon the date of a complete discontinuance of contributions to the Plan, an affected Participant&#146;s right to his or her Account balance shall be 100% Nonforfeitable to the extent
funded and required by the Code. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">15.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">MERGER </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee shall not consent to, or be a party to, any merger or consolidation with another plan, or
to a transfer of assets or liabilities to another plan, unless immediately after the merger, consolidation, or transfer, the surviving Plan provides each Participant a benefit equal to or greater than the benefit each Participant would have received
had the Plan terminated immediately before the merger, consolidation, or transfer. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">15.8</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">TERMINATION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Upon termination of the Plan, the provisions of the Article entitled &#147;Distribution of
Benefits,&#148; shall remain operative, and the Trust shall continue until the Trustee has distributed all of the benefits under the Plan. On each Anniversary Date or other Valuation Date, the Plan Administrator shall credit any part of a
Participant&#146;s Account balance retained in the Trust with its proportionate share of the Trust&#146;s income, expenses, gains, and losses, both realized and unrealized. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Article 16 General Provisions </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">EVIDENCE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Anyone required to give evidence under the terms of the Plan may do so by certificate, affidavit,
document, or other information that the Plan Administrator may consider pertinent, reliable, and genuine, and to have been signed, made, or presented by the proper party or parties. Any action required of the Employer may be by resolution of the
Employer, or by resolution or action of a person or entity authorized hereunder to act on behalf of the Employer. The Plan Administrator shall be fully protected in acting and relying upon any evidence described in this section. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 42</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">NO RESPONSIBILITY FOR EMPLOYER ACTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan Administrator shall have no obligation or responsibility with
respect to (a)&nbsp;any action required by the Plan to be taken by a Participating Employer, any Participant, or eligible Employee, (b)&nbsp;the failure of any of the above persons to act or make any payment or contribution, or to otherwise provide
any benefit contemplated under this Plan, or (c)&nbsp;the collection of any contribution required under the Plan or the determination of the correctness of the amount of any employer contribution. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FIDUCIARY DUTIES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan Administrator and any other person who has any fiduciary responsibility with respect
to the Plan shall discharge its duties and responsibilities with respect to the Plan in accordance with the Act, the regulations thereunder, and other applicable law. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">BENEFITS NOT INSURED </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee, the Plan Administrator, and Participating Employers in no way guarantee the
Trust Fund from loss or depreciation. Participating Employers do not guarantee the payment of any money which may be or become due to any person from the Trust Fund. The liability of the Plan Administrator and the Trustee to make any payment from
the Trust Fund at any time and all times is limited to the then-available assets of the Trust. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">WAIVER OF NOTICE AND SUCCESSORS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">To the extent permitted by law, any person entitled to notice under the Plan
may waive the notice. The Plan shall be binding upon all persons entitled to benefits under the Plan, their respective heirs and legal representatives, upon Participating Employers, their successors and assigns, and upon the Trustee, the Plan
Administrator, and their successors. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.6</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">MILITARY LEAVES OF ABSENCE </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Benefit Rights</U>. If a Participant returns from a Military Leave under circumstances that entitle the Participant to reemployment rights under the Uniformed Services Employment and Reemployment Rights Act of 1994,
notwithstanding any provision of this Plan to the contrary, contributions, benefits and service credit with respect to qualified military service will be provided in accordance with Section&nbsp;414(u) of the Code. If a Participant on Military Leave
dies or becomes Totally Disabled while performing qualified military service on or after January&nbsp;1, 2007, contributions shall be provided in accordance with Section&nbsp;414(u)(9) of the Code, and such Participant shall be treated as having
died or become Totally Disabled while employed by a Participating Employer for purposes of full vesting under Section&nbsp;8.1 and as otherwise required under Section&nbsp;401(a)(37) of the Code. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Distribution Rights</U>. In accordance with Section&nbsp;414(u)(12) of the Code, if a Participant goes on active duty Military Leave for a period exceeding 30 days, the Participant may apply for distribution of all
or a portion of the funds in his or her Salary Deferral Account. Any Participant who elects to receive a distribution under this subsection may not make Salary Deferral Contributions to the Plan for a period of 6 months following the date the
distribution is posted to the Participant&#146;s account. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">16.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">GOVERNING LAW </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan shall be construed, administered, and enforced according to the laws of the State of
Washington, to the extent not superseded by the Code, ERISA, or other federal law. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Article 17 Top-Heavy Provisions </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">17.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">TOP-HEAVY PROVISIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following provisions should become effective in any Plan Year in which the Plan is
determined to be a Top-Heavy Plan. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">17.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">TOP-HEAVY DEFINITIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Determination Date</U>&#148; means the last day of the preceding Plan Year or the last day of the first Plan Year. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 43</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Key Employee</U>&#148; means each Employee or former Employee (including a Beneficiary of a Key Employee) who, at any time during the current Plan Year or any of the four immediately preceding Plan Years, is or
was (i)&nbsp;an officer of a Participating Employer earning Section&nbsp;415 Compensation of more than 50% of the amount specified in Section&nbsp;415(b)(1)(A) of the Code for such Plan Year, (ii)&nbsp;among the 10 Employees owning, or considered as
owning within the meaning of Section&nbsp;318 of the Code, the largest interests (at least 0.5%) in the Participating Employer and earning Section&nbsp;415 Compensation of more than the amount specified in Section&nbsp;415(c)(1)(A) of the Code for
such Plan Year, (iii)&nbsp;a Five Percent Owner of the Participating Employer, or (iv)&nbsp;an Employee owning more than 1% of the Participating Employer and receiving more than $150,000 of annual Section&nbsp;415 Compensation from the Participating
Employer. Notwithstanding the foregoing, no more than 50 Employees or, if less, the greater of three or 10% of the Participating Employer&#146;s Employees shall be treated as officers of the Participating Employer. Effective January&nbsp;1, 2002,
&#147;Key Employee&#148; means each Employee or former Employee (including a Beneficiary of a Key Employee) who at any time during the current Plan Year is or was (i)&nbsp;an officer of the Participating Employer earning Section&nbsp;415
Compensation greater than $130,000 for such Plan Year (as adjusted under Code Section&nbsp;416(i)(1) for Plan Years beginning after December&nbsp;31, 2002), (ii)&nbsp;a Five Percent Owner of the Participating Employer, or (iii)&nbsp;an Employee
owning 1% of the Participating Employer and receiving more than $150,000 of annual Section&nbsp;415 Compensation from the Participating Employer. Notwithstanding the foregoing, no more than 50 Employees, or, if less, the greater of three or 10% of
the Participating Employer&#146;s Employees shall be treated as officers of the Participating Employer. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Non-Key Employee</U>&#148; means any Employee who is not a Key Employee. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Permissive Aggregation Group</U>&#148; means the Required Aggregation Group plus any other plan or plans of the Participating Employer which, when considered as a group with the Required Aggregation Group,
would continue to satisfy the requirements of Sections 401(a)(4) and 410 of the Code. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(e)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Required Aggregation Group</U>&#148; means (i)&nbsp;each qualified plan of the Participating Employer in which at least one Key Employee participates or participated at any time during the determination period
(regardless of whether the plan terminated), and (ii)&nbsp;any other qualified plan of the Participating Employer which enables a plan described in (i)&nbsp;to meet the requirements of Sections 401(a)(4) or 410 of the Code. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(f)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<U>Top-Heavy Valuation Date</U>&#148; means the most recent Anniversary Date that falls within or ends with the 12-month period ending on the Determination Date. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">17.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DETERMINATION OF TOP-HEAVY STATUS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan shall be considered a Top-Heavy Plan for the Plan Year if, as of
the Determination Date: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Top-Heavy Ratio for this Plan exceeds 60% and this Plan is not part of any Required Aggregation Group or Permissive Aggregation Group; or </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">This Plan is a part of a Required Aggregation Group but is not part of a Permissive Aggregation Group and the Top-Heavy Ratio for the group of plans exceeds 60%; or </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">This Plan is part of a Required Aggregation Group and part of a Permissive Aggregation Group and the Top-Heavy Ratio for the Permissive Aggregation Group exceeds 60%. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">17.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">TOP-HEAVY RATIO </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participating Employer maintains one or more defined contribution plans (including this Plan and any simplified employee pension plan) and the Participating Employer has not maintained any defined benefit plan
which during the five-year period ending on the Determination Date has or has had accrued benefits, the Top-Heavy Ratio for this Plan alone or for the Required or Permissive Aggregation Group as appropriate shall be a fraction, the numerator of
which is the sum of the account balances of all Key Employees as of the Determination Date, and the denominator of which is the sum of all account balances for all Employees, both computed in accordance with Section&nbsp;416 of the Code. Both the
numerator and the denominator of the Top-Heavy Ratio shall be adjusted to reflect any contribution not actually made as of the Determination Date, but which is required to be taken into account on that date under Section&nbsp;416 of the Code.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><I>Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right">Page 44</TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participating Employer maintains one or more defined contribution plans (including this Plan and any simplified employee pension plan) and the Participating Employer maintains or has maintained one or more
defined benefit plans which, during the five-year period ending on the Determination Date, has or has had any accrued benefits, the Top-Heavy Ratio for any Required or Permissive Aggregation Group as appropriate shall be a fraction, the numerator of
which is the sum of account balances under the aggregated defined contribution plan or plans for all Key Employees, determined in accordance with subparagraph (a)&nbsp;above, together with the present value of accrued benefits under the defined
benefit plan or plans for all Employees as of the Determination Date, and the denominator of which is the sum of the account balances under the aggregated defined contribution plan or plans for all Employees, determined in accordance with
subparagraph (a)&nbsp;above, together with the present value of accrued benefits under the defined benefit plan or plans for all Employees as of the Determination Date, all determined in accordance with Section&nbsp;416 of the Code.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For purposes of subparagraphs (a)&nbsp;and (b)&nbsp;above, the value of account balances and the present value of accrued benefits shall be determined as of the Top-Heavy Valuation Date, except as provided in
Section&nbsp;416 of the Code for the first and second plan years of a defined benefit plan and using the same actuarial equivalent for all defined benefit plans. The account balances and accrued benefits of any Participant who has not been credited
with at least one Hour of Service with any Participating Employer maintaining the Plan at any time during the one year period ending on the Determination Date shall be disregarded. The calculation of the Top-Heavy Ratio, and the extent to which
account balances, accrued benefits, distributions, rollovers, and transfers are taken into account shall be made in accordance with Sections 416(g)(4)(A), (B)&nbsp;and (E)&nbsp;of the Code. Deductible Employee Contributions shall not be taken into
account for purposes of computing the Top-Heavy Ratio. When aggregating plans, the value of account balances and accrued benefits shall be calculated with reference to the Determination Dates that fall within the same calendar year. The amounts of
account balances and the present value of accrued benefits of an Employee as of the Determination Date shall be increased by the distributions made with respect to the Employee under the Plan and any plan aggregated with the Plan under
Section&nbsp;416(g)(2) of the Code during one-year period ending on the Determination Date. The preceding sentence shall also apply to distributions under a terminated plan which, if it had not been terminated, would have been aggregated with the
Plan under Section&nbsp;416(g)(2)(A)(i) of the Code. In the case of a distribution made for a reason other than separation from service, death, or disability, this provision shall be applied substituting &#147;five-year period&#148; for
&#147;one-year period.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">17.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">MINIMUM ALLOCATION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Except as otherwise provided in subparagraphs (b)&nbsp;and (c)&nbsp;below, the Participating Employer contributions and forfeitures allocated on behalf of any Participant who is not a Key Employee shall not be less than
the lesser of 3% of such Participant&#146;s Section&nbsp;415 Compensation or, in the case where the Participating Employer has no defined benefit plan which designates this Plan to satisfy Section&nbsp;401 of the Code, the largest percentage of
Participating Employer contributions (including Salary Deferral Contributions) and forfeitures, as a percentage of the Key Employee&#146;s Section&nbsp;415 Compensation, as limited by Section&nbsp;401(a)(17) of the Code, allocated on behalf of any
Key Employee for that Plan Year (the &#147;Minimum Allocation&#148;). The Minimum Allocation shall be made even though, under other Plan provisions, the Participant would not otherwise be entitled to receive an allocation, or would have received a
lesser allocation for the Plan Year because (i)&nbsp;the Non-Key Employee failed to complete 1,000 Hours of Service (or any equivalent provided in the Plan), (ii)&nbsp;the Non-Key Employee failed to make mandatory employee contributions to the Plan,
(iii)&nbsp;the Non-Key Employee&#146;s Section&nbsp;415 Compensation is less than a stated amount, or (iv)&nbsp;the Plan is integrated with Social Security. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The provision in subparagraph (a)&nbsp;above shall not apply to any Participant who was not employed by the Participating Employer on the last day of the Plan Year. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Participating Employer maintains a defined benefit plan as well as this Plan, the Minimum Allocation required by this Paragraph shall be increased to 5% of the Section&nbsp;415 Compensation of the Participant.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Minimum Allocation required (to the extent required to be Nonforfeitable under Section&nbsp;416(b) of the Code) may not be forfeited under Sections 411(a)(3)(B) or 411(a)(3)(D) of the Code. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(e)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Matching Contributions shall be taken into account for purposes of satisfying the minimum contribution requirements of Section&nbsp;416(c)(2) of the Code and the Plan. The preceding sentence shall apply with respect to
Matching Contributions under the Plan or, if the Plan provides that the minimum contribution requirement shall be met in another plan, matching contributions under such other plan. Matching Contributions that are used to satisfy the minimum
contribution requirements shall be treated as matching contributions for purposes of the actual contribution percentage test and other requirements of Section&nbsp;401(m) of the Code. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">MINIMUM VESTING IN TOP-HEAVY YEARS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Notwithstanding the normal vesting schedule described in Section&nbsp;8.2,
in Top-Heavy Years a Participant who has completed at least one Hour of Service in the Top-Heavy Year shall be vested with a percentage portion of that Participant&#146;s Matching Contribution Account, and Discretionary and Company Contribution
Accounts, in accordance with the following Vesting Schedule: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Service for Vesting may elect within a reasonable period whether to continue with the vesting schedule applicable in the Top-Heavy year or return to the normal vesting schedule described in Section&nbsp;8.2. In addition, the portion of the account
of any Participant that was nonforfeitable before the Plan ceased to be Top-Heavy shall remain nonforfeitable. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>APPENDIX B &#150; Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Pay Summary Group Chart </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">January&nbsp;1, 2010 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Definitions of Compensation by Pay Summary Groups &#150; Jan. 2010 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>X = Include O = Exclude </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000; width:4.00pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>#</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Pay Summary Group</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>APPENDIX C &#150; Eligibility Requirements for the </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Wellness Assessment Contribution </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Each
Employee who is in Eligible Employment and who meets all of the following eligibility requirements shall be entitled to receive a &#147;Wellness Assessment Contribution,&#148; which shall be a Profit Sharing Contribution under the Plan: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must be a Non-Highly Compensated Employee for the 2007 Plan Year; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In 2007, the Employee must complete and submit the Health Assessment administered by Aetna; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must be identified on Costco&#146;s payroll system as working at a Costco location in the 48 contiguous United States or Alaska as of the date the Employee completes and submits the Health Assessment; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must be eligible for and participating in a medical plan under the Costco Employee Benefits Program as of the date the Employee completes and submits the Health Assessment. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Eligibility Requirements for the 2007 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Costco Employee Benefits Program Contribution </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Each Employee who is in Eligible Employment and who meets all of the following eligibility requirements shall be entitled to receive a 2007 Costco Employee
Benefits Program Contribution, which is a Profit Sharing Contribution under the Plan: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must have been eligible for the Costco Employee Benefits Program at the end of the fiscal year ending in 2007, to-wit: September&nbsp;2, 2007 (and eligibility for coverage must not have ended as of that
date, as described in pages 20-21 of the Costco Employee Benefits Program Summary Plan Description); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must be in Eligible Employment on September&nbsp;2, 2007 and on December&nbsp;31, 2007; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employee must not be an Insider (as defined in Section&nbsp;7.2 of the Plan). </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 99.1A </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;1 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to amend and restate the Plan to permit partial and installment distributions in certain
circumstances; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">PARTICIPANT ROLLOVER CONTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant who is also an Eligible Employee, with the Plan
Administrator&#146;s consent and after filing with the Trustee the form prescribed by the Plan Administrator, may contribute cash or other property to the Trust other than as a voluntary contribution if the contribution is a qualified &#147;rollover
contribution&#148; which the Code permits an Employee to transfer from a qualified plan, from a Code Section&nbsp;403(a) annuity plan or 403(b) tax-sheltered annuity contract or from a Code Section&nbsp;457(b) qualified deferred compensation plan,
to another qualified plan (&#147;Rollover Contribution&#148;), as long as the Rollover Contribution does not include after-tax contributions and will not require any changes to the operation and administration of this Plan or the provision of any
form of distribution<U> not otherwise permitted under the terms of the terms of the Plan</U><STRIKE> other than a lump sum distribution</STRIKE>. The Plan does not accept rollovers from a Participant&#146;s Roth elective deferral account in another
plan. Before accepting a Rollover Contribution, the Trustee may require an Employee to furnish satisfactory evidence that the proposed transfer first in fact a qualified Rollover Contribution that is acceptable to the Plan. If a contribution is made
to the Trust under this section, the Trustee shall hold the amount contributed in a segregated Account for the Participant&#146;s sole benefit. The interest of each Participant in all such Employee Contribution Accounts shall be 100% vested and
Nonforfeitable at all times. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FORM OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The normal form of benefit shall be a single-sum distribution of the Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance, which shall be made to the Participant, if living, or if not, to the Participant&#146;s surviving Spouse, but if there is no surviving Spouse or if the Spouse has consented in a manner conforming to Section&nbsp;13.1,
then to the Participant&#146;s designated Beneficiary. The distribution shall be made as a lump-sum payment in cash, with the exception of the portion of an account invested in Employer Stock, with respect to which the Participant may elect a
distribution in kind. There shall be no installment form of distribution except as <U>permitted by a retirement income manager program adopted by the Employer, or as </U>provided under Section&nbsp;9.6 with respect to required minimum distributions.
Any partial distribution permitted or required under the Plan shall be made on a pro-rata basis from all of the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts and investment funds, except that required minimum distributions shall be made from a
Participant&#146;s Roth Elective Deferral Account only after complete distribution from all other accounts and correction of excess Annual Additions shall be made in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.4. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.8</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">HARDSHIP DISTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A current Employee who is also a Participant may request a <U>lump sum </U>distribution
of funds from the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account in the event of certain financial hardships, if the distribution meets the requirements of this section and the deemed hardship distribution standards of Treasury Regulation
1.401(k)-1(d)(3) (as modified by subsequent laws). The amount of a hardship distribution shall not exceed Salary Deferral Contributions (excluding amounts received as a loan), excluding earnings. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">*** </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.11</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">NOTICE AND CONSENT TO DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">*** </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 1 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated 1/1/2011 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"> Page
 2
 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Rollover Notice</U>: No less than 30 days and no more than 180 days before the date of a distribution that is an eligible rollover distribution (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9), the Plan Administrator shall provide
the distributee (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9) of such distribution with the notice described in Section&nbsp;402(f) of the Code or, in accordance with Treasury Regulations, a summary of that notice. Notwithstanding the above, distribution may be
made less than 30 days after such notice or summary is given, provided that: (1)&nbsp;the Plan Administrator clearly informs the distributee that the distributee has a right to a period of at least 30 days after receiving the notice or summary to
consider the decision of whether or not to elect a direct rollover, and (2)&nbsp;the distributee, after receiving the notice or summary, affirmatively elects a distribution. <U>In the case of a series of installment payments that are eligible
rollover distributions, the rules of this subparagraph shall apply only to the first such installment payment, in accordance with Section&nbsp;402(f) of the Code and applicable Treasury Regulations.</U> </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">10.1 LOAN PROGRAM </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may borrow limited amounts from
the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account (excluding his or her Roth Elective Deferral Account), Matching Contribution Account (to the extent vested), Profit Sharing Contribution Account, any Nondeductible Voluntary Contribution Account
established under a Prior Plan, and any Rollover Account established under Section&nbsp;6.1 (referred to collectively in this Article as &#147;eligible accounts&#148;). Participant loans shall not be made from a Participant&#146;s Company or
Discretionary Contribution Accounts, ESOP Dividend Reinvestment Account, Rescission Account, Qualified Non-Elective Contribution Account, Roth Elective Deferral Account, or from the non-vested portion of the Participant&#146;s Matching Contribution
Account. <U>Participant loans are made only in the form of a lump sum. </U>Only one loan from the plan may be outstanding at any time, and outstanding loans may not be amended or refinanced. Moreover, a Participant who has an outstanding loan from
any other plan of a Participating Employer is not eligible for a loan from this Plan until the loan to the other plan is repaid in full. In the event of default on a plan loan, a Participant may not apply for another loan earlier than six months
after the defaulted loan is repaid in full. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">*** </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">This
Amendment is effective February&nbsp;1, 2011, or such later date as is administratively practicable. Jay Tihinen and John Matthews are further authorized to make further changes to the Plan and its administrative policies to adopt a retirement
income manager program, including notice, consent, and distribution requirements. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;2 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to update the Plan&#146;s Pay Summary Group Chart; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Pay Summary Group Chart is updated effective January&nbsp;1, 2011, as attached hereto. Jay Tihinen is delegated power
to further update the Chart. </P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;3 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to may certain changes to the Plan; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B></B>1.66</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<B>Salary Deferral Agreement</B>&#148; means a written agreement or enrollment form (or written confirmation of a voice enrollment) in which a Participant elects to have his or her Compensation reduced by a
specified amount in whole percentages, or elects not to have his or her Compensation reduced. Salary Deferral Agreement also means a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduced by 3% under &#147;Automatic
Enrollment&#148; as described below and a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduction percentage increased under &#147;Automatic Increases&#148; as described below. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for
non-Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. These limits apply to pre-tax
Contributions and Roth Elective Deferrals combined. The determination of whether a contribution is a Catch-Up Contribution is, however, determined in accordance with Section&nbsp;3.1(e) and Code Section&nbsp;414(v). Salary Deferral Agreements shall
be governed by the following:<B> </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Automatic Increases</U>. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="16%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(i)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Except as provided in (ii)&nbsp;below, the Compensation reduction percentage in an Eligible Employee&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement shall be automatically increased by 1% on each anniversary of the Employee&#146;s
Employment Commencement Date (or re-employment date, if applicable), unless the Employee suspends or amends his or her Salary Deferral Agreement during the 30-day period ending on such anniversary date. Such increase is considered an amendment to
the Employee&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement, and is effective on the first day of the pay period (or extended pay period as provided in Section (a)) ending after the Employee&#146;s anniversary date described above. This automatic increase shall
not apply if the Compensation reduction percentage in the Employee&#146;s then-existing Salary Deferral Agreement is either 0% or is <U>20</U><STRIKE>15</STRIKE>% or more. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="16%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(ii)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">An Employee may elect to not have automatic increases apply to his or her Salary Deferral Agreement. In addition, an Employee may elect to change the manner in which the automatic increase described in (i), above,
applies to his or her Salary Deferral Agreement by (A)&nbsp;choosing a different date for scheduled automatic increases; (B)&nbsp;choosing a different whole percentage of compensation for the amount of automatic increases; and/or (C)&nbsp;choosing a
different maximum Compensation reduction percentage for automatic increases. An Employee&#146;s election to opt out of automatic increases or to change the manner in which automatic increases apply must be made by such method as the Plan
Administrator may announce, from time to time (including an automated voice response or other electronic medium), and on or before such reasonable prior deadline as the Plan Administrator shall establish from time to time. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 3 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 2 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">13.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION TO BENEFICIARIES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Each Participant shall designate his or her Beneficiaries on the Beneficiary
designation form provided by the Plan as either primary or secondary. Secondary Beneficiaries who survive the Participant are entitled to a distribution of a deceased Participant&#146;s Account only if no primary Beneficiary survives the
Participant. Beneficiaries shall receive the percentage of the Account specified by the Participant on the form. If more than one Beneficiary is designated but no percentage is specified, the Beneficiaries entitled to a distribution shall receive
the deceased Participant&#146;s Account in equal shares. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If the Participant does not designate a Beneficiary, or if all primary and secondary
Beneficiaries <STRIKE>predecease </STRIKE><U>do not survive </U>the Participant, the Trustee shall pay the Participant&#146;s Account balance<U> to his or her default Beneficiary as determined</U> in the following order of priority: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant&#146;s surviving Spouse; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant&#146;s <U>surviving </U>issue, including adopted children, in equal shares, by right of representation; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><U>(c)</U></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>The Participant&#146;s surviving parents, in equal shares; </U> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><U>(d)</U></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>The Participant&#146;s siblings, in equal shares; or</U> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><U>(e)</U><STRIKE>(c)</STRIKE></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant&#146;s estate, provided, however, that if the Plan Administrator cannot locate a qualified representative of the deceased Participant&#146;s estate or if no such representative has been appointed by an
appropriate court, then the Participant&#146;s heirs-at-law as determined in the reasonable judgment of the Plan Administrator. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If none of
the foregoing can be located, the deceased Participant&#146;s account shall be treated as an Unclaimed Account under Section&nbsp;14.5. For purposes of determining rights to distribution of an Account under this Section, an Alternate Payee of a
Participant shall be treated as a Participant and not as a Beneficiary. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If a Beneficiary survives the Participant but dies before distribution in full of
the Participant&#146;s Account, the remaining Account shall be distributed to the surviving beneficiary or beneficiaries designated by the Beneficiary on a form provided by the Plan Administrator. If no beneficiary is designated by the Beneficiary,
or if <U>all primary and secondary beneficiaries </U><STRIKE>the beneficiary </STRIKE>designated by the Beneficiary <STRIKE>predeceases </STRIKE><U>do not survive </U>the Beneficiary, the Account shall be distributed to the estate of the
Beneficiary. The procedures described in the first paragraph of this Section&nbsp;13.2 shall apply to beneficiary designations of Beneficiaries. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Effective Dates:</I></B> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Changes to Section&nbsp;1.66 are effective September&nbsp;1, 2012, or when administratively practicable thereafter. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Changes to Section&nbsp;13.2 adding new default beneficiary categories are effective for deaths occurring on or after June&nbsp;11, 2012; other changes to Section&nbsp;13.2 clarify the Plan. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;4 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to update the Plan&#146;s Pay Summary Group Chart; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Pay Summary Group Chart is updated effective January&nbsp;1, 2012, as attached hereto. Jay Tihinen is delegated power
to further update the Chart. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;5 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to make certain changes to the Plan; </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">NOW,&nbsp;THEREFORE,</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B></B>1.66</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<B>Salary Deferral Agreement</B>&#148; means a written agreement or enrollment form (or written confirmation of a voice enrollment) in which a Participant elects to have his or her Compensation reduced by a
specified amount in whole percentages, or elects not to have his or her Compensation reduced. Salary Deferral Agreement also means a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduced by 3% under &#147;Automatic
Enrollment&#148; as described below and a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduction percentage increased under &#147;Automatic Increases&#148; as described below. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for
non-Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. These limits apply to pre-tax
Contributions and Roth Elective Deferrals combined. The determination of whether a contribution is a Catch-Up Contribution is, however, determined in accordance with Section&nbsp;3.1(e) and Code Section&nbsp;414(v). Salary Deferral Agreements shall
be governed by the following:<B> </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U><B>Automatic Enrollment</B></U>. If an Employee is eligible to make Salary Deferral Contributions but does not submit a Salary Deferral Agreement before the dates in (i)&nbsp;or (ii)&nbsp;below (as applicable), <U>or
within the period specified in (iii), below (in the case of a currently eligible Employee who has made a 0% Salary Deferral Agreement), </U>the Employee will be automatically enrolled in the Plan and treated as having submitted a Salary Deferral
Agreement electing to have his or her Compensation reduced by 3%. Automatic Enrollment is effective on the first day of the pay period (or extended pay period as provided in Section (a)) ending after the following: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">(i) For Employees who become eligible for Salary Deferral Contributions on their Entry Date (as described in
Section&nbsp;2.1),the 30-day period following the first day of the month after they complete 90 days of Service within a 12-consecutive-month period<STRIKE>. </STRIKE><U>; </U> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">(ii) For Employees who become eligible for Salary Deferral Contributions upon re-hire (as described in Section&nbsp;2.4) or
upon entering Eligible Employment (as described in Section&nbsp;2.1), the 30-day period following the date they become eligible under Section&nbsp;2.1 or 2.4<STRIKE>.</STRIKE><U>; and</U> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><U>(iii) Such times as specified in rules adopted by the Committee or its delegate acting in a Plan Sponsor capacity.</U> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 5 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 2 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>7.5</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>INVESTMENT IN EMPLOYER STOCK</B> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The following shall apply to dividends payable on Employer Stock held in the ESOP: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * *
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Dividends on Employer Stock held in one or more ESOP funds may be distributed to Participants as follows: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(i)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Employer may notify the Plan Administrator from time to time that it intends to distribute dividends on Employer Stock to Participants in the ESOP. Thereafter, the Employer shall either pay the dividends in cash
directly to Participants, or it shall pay the dividends to the Trust and the Trustee shall distribute the dividends in cash to Participants. If dividends are paid to the Trust, they shall be distributed to Participants by the Trustee at such time
and with such frequency as directed by the Plan Administrator, but in no event later than 90 days after the end of the Plan Year in which the dividends are paid to the Trust. The Employer&#146;s notice to the Plan Administrator herein shall apply
only to dividends with a record date after the Plan Administrator receives the Employer&#146;s notice. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(ii)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If the Plan Administrator receives the notice described above, it may provide to ESOP Participants a continuing election to either receive the dividends allocable to their Accounts in cash or reinvest the dividends in
Employer Stock. The initial election shall be provided and shall become irrevocable, as determined by the Plan Administrator with notice to Participants, within a reasonable period of time before a dividend is paid, and thereafter Participants shall
have a reasonable opportunity to change their elections at least annually. If a Participant fails to make an election, the Participant shall be deemed to have elected to reinvest dividends in Employer Stock. <U>Notwithstanding the foregoing, the
Plan Administrator may, from time to time, reset Participant elections to reinvest the dividends paid on Employer Stock. Any such reset will be made only upon advance notice to Participants within a reasonable period of time before a dividend is
paid, and shall provide Participants with a reasonable opportunity to make a continuing election with respect to dividends payable after such notice, to receive the dividends allocable to their Accounts in cash, and thereafter Participants shall
have a reasonable opportunity to change their elections at least annually. </U>Dividends reinvested in Employer Stock at the election or deemed election of a Participant shall be 100% vested. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(iii)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">If dividends are to be paid directly to Participants, the Plan Administrator shall provide the Employer with information reasonably requested by the Employer for the purpose of identifying Participants entitled to a
distribution with respect to shares allocated to their Accounts as of the dividend record date. If dividends are to be paid from the Trust or reinvested, the amount paid to each Participant or the amount reinvested shall be equal to the amount of
the dividend with respect to shares allocated to the Participant&#146;s Account as of the dividend record date. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">**** </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>9.11</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>NOTICE AND CONSENT TO DISTRIBUTION</B> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">**** </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Automatic Rollovers</U>: In the event of a mandatory distribution to a Participant greater than $1,000 <U>from their Roth Elective Deferral Account, or from all other Plan Accounts (combined), </U>in accordance with
the provisions of Section&nbsp;9.11(a), if the Participant does not elect to have such distribution paid directly to an eligible retirement plan specified by the Participant in a direct rollover or to receive the distribution directly, then the Plan
Administrator shall pay the distribution in a direct rollover to an individual retirement plan designated by the Plan Administrator. </TD></TR></TABLE>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
