<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;6 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to add CWC DC LLC, a wholly owned LLC of Costco Wholesale Corporation, as a Participating
Employer under the Plan; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P>

entities are Participating Employers: </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco Wholesale Corporation </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco Wholesale Membership, Inc. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">CWC Travel, Inc. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><U>CWC DC LLC</U> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Effective Date: </I></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;7 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to change certain provisions concerning distributions and loans; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following change is made to Section&nbsp;4.1: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION OF EXCESS DEFERRALS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Excess Deferrals and income or loss allocable thereto shall be distributed no
later than each April&nbsp;15 to Participants who make a timely claim for such Excess Deferrals for the preceding calendar year. The income or loss allocable to Excess Deferrals shall be the product of the income or loss allocable to the
Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account (and other amounts treated as elective contributions under the Code) for the preceding calendar year multiplied by a fraction, the numerator of which is the Participant&#146;s Excess Deferral for the
preceding calendar year and the denominator of which is the sum of (i)&nbsp;the Participant&#146;s Account balance attributable to Salary Deferral Contributions (and other amounts treated as elective contributions under the Code) determined as of
the beginning of the preceding calendar year and (ii)&nbsp;the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Contributions (and other amounts treated as elective contributions under the Code) for the preceding calendar year. A Participant&#146;s claim for
Excess Deferrals must be in writing and shall be submitted to the Plan Administrator no later than <U>April </U><STRIKE>March</STRIKE>&nbsp;1 of the year following the calendar year in which such Excess Deferrals were made. If, after distribution of
Excess Deferrals, the effective availability rule of Treasury Regulation 1.401(a)(4)-4(c) is not met for a Highly Compensated Employee, Matching Contributions attributable to such Excess Deferrals plus any income and any loss allocable thereto shall
be distributed to such Highly Compensated Employee(s) as wages; provided, however, that if such distribution is prohibited by Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;401(m), then such amounts shall instead be forfeited and allocated in the same manner as
provided in Section&nbsp;8.4. The income and loss allocable to such Matching Contributions shall be calculated using a methodology similar to that described above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following clarification is made to Section&nbsp;7.1(d): </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">7.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">INVESTMENT OF ACCOUNTS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#133;. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Investment Funds.</U> The Plan Administrator shall select the Investment Funds and monitor their performance. The Investment Funds shall include at least three diversified funds which have materially different risk
and return characteristics. <U>Participants (and Beneficiaries in the case of deceased Participants, and Alternate Payees) </U><STRIKE>Each Investment Fund sponsor </STRIKE>shall <U>be </U>provide<U>d</U><STRIKE> prospectuses and other
</STRIKE>disclosures required by <U>the Act, including </U><STRIKE>regulations under </STRIKE>Section&nbsp;404(c) of the Act<STRIKE>, and the Plan Administrator shall take appropriate steps to assure that Participants (and Beneficiaries, in the case
of deceased Participants) will receive the information and disclosure required by such regulations</STRIKE>. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 7 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 2 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following changes are made to Article 9: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FORM OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The normal form of benefit shall be a single-sum distribution of the Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance, which shall be made to the Participant, if living, or if not, to the Participant&#146;s surviving Spouse, but if there is no surviving Spouse or if the Spouse has consented in a manner conforming to Section&nbsp;13.1,
then to the Participant&#146;s designated Beneficiary. The distribution shall be made as a lump-sum payment in cash, with the exception of the portion of an account invested in Employer Stock, with respect to which the Participant may elect a
distribution in kind. Any partial distribution permitted or required under the Plan shall be made on a pro-rata basis from all of the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts and investment funds, except<U>: (1)&nbsp;a Participant may designate the
portion of a partial distribution to be made from the Participant&#146;s Roth Deferral Account or from all of his or her other accounts; (2)</U><STRIKE>&nbsp;that</STRIKE> required minimum distributions shall be made from a Participant&#146;s Roth
Elective Deferral Account only after complete distribution from all other accounts<U>;</U> and <U>(3)</U>&nbsp;correction of excess Annual Additions shall be made in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.4. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.8</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">HARDSHIP DISTRIBUTIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A current Employee who is also a Participant may request a lump sum distribution of
funds from the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account in the event of certain financial hardships, if the distribution meets the requirements of this section and the deemed hardship distribution standards of Treasury Regulation 1.401(k)-1(d)(3)
(as modified by subsequent laws). The amount of a hardship distribution shall not exceed Salary Deferral Contributions (excluding amounts received as a loan), excluding earnings. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must satisfy the deemed immediate and heavy financial need requirements of Treasury Regulations, which at present constitute the following financial needs: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expenses for (or necessary to obtain) medical care that would be deductible under Code Section&nbsp;213(d) (determined without regard to whether the expenses exceed 7.5% of adjusted gross income); </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Costs directly related to the purchase of a principal residence for the Participant (excluding mortgage payments); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payment of tuition, related educational fees, and room and board expenses, for up to the next 12 months of post-secondary education for the Participant, or the Participant&#146;s spouse, children, or dependents (as
defined in Code Section&nbsp;152 without regard to Section&nbsp;152(b)(1), (b)(2) and (d)(1)(B)); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payments necessary to prevent the eviction of the Participant from the Participant&#146;s principal residence or foreclosure on the mortgage on that residence. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Payments for burial or funeral expenses for the Participant&#146;s deceased parent, spouse, children or dependents (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;152 without regard to Code Section&nbsp;152(d)(1)(B)); or
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(6)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Expenses for the repair of damage to the Participant&#146;s principal residence that would qualify for the casualty deduction determined under Code Section&nbsp;165 (determined without regard to whether the loss exceeds
10% of adjusted gross income). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must be deemed necessary to satisfy an immediate and heavy financial need of the Participant under Treasury Regulations. Those Treasury Regulations at present require: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant has obtained all other currently available distributions (including distributions of ESOP dividends under Code Section&nbsp;404(k), but not hardship distributions), and nontaxable (at the time of the
loan) loans, under this Plan and all other plans maintained by Participating Employers; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Participant may make no further Salary Deferral Contributions (or any other employee contributions) to this Plan or to any other plans maintained by Participating Employers for a period of 6 months from the date the
hardship distribution is posted to the Participant&#146;s Account by the Trustee (the &#147;suspension period&#148;). </TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 7 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 3 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For purposes of this Section&nbsp;<U>9.8</U><STRIKE>8.2</STRIKE>(b), the phrase &#147;plans
maintained by Participating Employers&#148; means all qualified and non-qualified plans of deferred compensation maintained by Participating Employers. However, the phrase does not include contributions to health or welfare benefit plans including
health and welfare plans that are part of a cafeteria plan within the meaning of Code Section&nbsp;125. In addition, for purposes of Section&nbsp;<U>9.8</U><STRIKE>8.2</STRIKE>(b)(2), the phrase also includes a stock option, stock purchase, or
similar plan maintained by a Participating Employer. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The distribution must not be in excess of the amount of the immediate and heavy financial need of the Participant. The amount of an immediate and heavy financial need may include any amounts necessary to pay any
federal, state, or local income taxes or penalties reasonably anticipated to result from the distribution. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">A Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Contributions to the Plan (other than Catch-Up Contributions) shall automatically resume effective the first day of the first pay period (or extended pay period as provided in
Section&nbsp;1.62(a)) ending at least 30 days following the end of the suspension period described in paragraph (b)(2), above, based on the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement last in effect prior to the suspension period. However, the
preceding sentence shall not apply to a Participant who, within 30 days following the end of the suspension period and in the manner required by the Plan Administrator, submits a Salary Deferral Agreement electing a different or no Compensation
reduction percentage. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">(e)<U> Notwithstanding anything in this Section&nbsp;9.8 to the contrary, pursuant to IRS Announcement 2012-44, a
hardship distribution may be made on account of any immediate and heavy financial need resulting from Hurricane Sandy, despite not satisfying the deemed immediate and heavy financial need requirements described under Section&nbsp;9.8(a) and the
Treasury Regulations, if such distribution is made (a)&nbsp;on or after October&nbsp;26, 2012 and no later than February&nbsp;1, 2013 and (b)&nbsp;to a current employee whose principal residence on October&nbsp;26, 2012, was located in one of the
counties or Tribal Nations of Connecticut, New Jersey, New York, or Rhode Island designated by the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) as a covered disaster area because of the devastation caused by Hurricane Sandy. All other requirements
provided under this Section&nbsp;9.8 and the Treasury Regulations shall apply.</U> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Section&nbsp;13.7 is clarified as follows: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">13.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">COMMUNICATIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Written communications to the Plan Administrator, the Plan, a Participating Employer, the
Trustee, the Committee or other fiduciaries, or their agents or representatives, must be received before the expiration of any time period expressed herein or in related documents (including the summary plan description and policies and procedures
for this Plan). <U>To the extent the Plan Administrator, the Trustee, a Participating Employer or the Plan approves the use of electronic or telephonic communications to or from Plan Participants (as permitted by the Code or the Act, as applicable),
and to the extent not otherwise prohibited or provided otherwise hereunder, such electronic or telephonic communications are treated as written communications hereunder. </U>The Plan Administrator&#146;s (or the Plan&#146;s, a Participating
Employer&#146;s, the Trustee&#146;s, the Committee&#146;s or other fiduciaries&#146;, as applicable), or their agents&#146; or representatives&#146; records will be conclusive as to whether a communication has been <U>sent or </U>received and the
date of such <U>sending or </U>receipt, unless the sender produces a United States Postal Service return receipt. The common law &#147;mailbox rule&#148; shall not apply to determine receipt or the date of receipt by the Plan Administrator (or the
Plan, a Participating Employer, the Trustee, the Committee or other fiduciaries, as applicable), or their agents or representatives. The common law mailbox rule shall apply for all other purposes under the Plan. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 7 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 4 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Section&nbsp;14.5 is reformed as follows: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">14.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">UNCLAIMED ACCOUNT PROCEDURES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan Administrator, by first class, certified or registered mail addressed in
accordance with Section&nbsp;13.4 hereof, shall notify Participants who have terminated employment and Beneficiaries of deceased Participants of their right to receive a distribution from the Plan. If such notice is returned as undeliverable, or if
a distribution check mailed to a Participant or Beneficiary is not cashed within six months after it is mailed, the Account of such Participant or Beneficiary will be deemed unclaimed (&#147;Unclaimed Account&#148;); provided Accounts that are
subject to automatic rollover under Section&nbsp;9.11(d) herein will not be treated as Unclaimed Accounts. The Plan Administrator shall take reasonable steps to locate the owner of an Unclaimed Account in accordance with procedures and policies
adopted by the Plan Administrator. Such steps may include<STRIKE> use of the IRS letter forwarding program,</STRIKE> use of a commercial locator service, or use of <U>a Federal agency</U><STRIKE>the Social Security Administration</STRIKE> search
program. After a six-month period during which reasonable steps have been taken to locate the lost Participant or Beneficiary, or such other period of time which is reasonable under the circumstances, if the lost Participant or Beneficiary has not
been located, the Plan Administrator may forfeit the Unclaimed Account. The amount forfeited shall include any interest, gains, or losses allocated to the Unclaimed Account during the search. Thereafter, if at any time before the Plan has been
terminated the lost Participant or Beneficiary makes a claim for his or her Account, the Plan Administrator shall restore the forfeited Account to the same dollar amount as the amount forfeited, unadjusted for gains or losses occurring subsequent to
the forfeiture. The Plan Administrator will make the restoration first from available forfeitures pursuant to Section&nbsp;8.4 hereof. If such forfeitures are not sufficient, a Participating Employer shall make an additional contribution to the Plan
in the amount necessary to restore the forfeited Account. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>The change to Section&nbsp;4.1 is effective for Excess Deferrals in Plan Year 2013
(distributed no later than April&nbsp;15, 2014). </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>The changes to Section&nbsp;9.3 are effective April&nbsp;8, 2013. </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>The changes to Section&nbsp;9.8 are effective October&nbsp;26, 2012. </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>The attached Pay Summary Group chart is effective January&nbsp;1, 2013, and any corrections or additions are effective the date as of which such new pay
summary group is corrected or updated on the Employer&#146;s payroll system. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>All other changes reform or clarify the Plan. </I></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;8 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to make a change to provisions concerning distributions; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following definition is added to Article 1: </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>&#147;Installment Distribution&#148; </B>means a distribution elected by a Participant, Beneficiary or alternate payee (as applicable) that
(1)&nbsp;requires equal payments to be made monthly, quarterly, or annually; (2)&nbsp;the distributee may, with written notice, terminate prospectively; (3)&nbsp;automatically terminates on death of the distributee; and (4)&nbsp;as to a Participant,
automatically terminates if the Participant is rehired. Single sum, lump sum, and partial distributions are not Installment Distributions. No Installment Distribution payment may exceed the distributee&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account Balance,
Section&nbsp;9.6 applies notwithstanding a distributee&#146;s election of Installment Distributions and once an Installment Distribution has begun, Section&nbsp;9.11(a) no longer applies to such Installment Distribution. <B> </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following changes are made to Article 9: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION AFTER SEVERANCE FROM EMPLOYMENT </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may apply for a distribution of <U>all or a portion
of, or for Installment Distributions from</U>, <STRIKE>the total</STRIKE> the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance at any time after severance of employment with all Participating Employers for any reason. Subject to
Section&nbsp;9.11(a), a Participant may, instead, delay distribution until distribution is required under Section&nbsp;9.6(a). </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">FORM OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The normal form of benefit shall be a single <U>lump</U> sum distribution of the
Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance<U>. A Participant may also elect distribution of a portion of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account Balance, and Installment Distributions may be elected for distributions other than those
under Sections 9.1 and 9.8.</U><STRIKE>, which shall be made to the Participant, if living, or if not, to the Participant&#146;s surviving Spouse, but if there is no surviving Spouse or if the Spouse has consented in a manner conforming to Section
13.1, then to the Participant&#146;s designated Beneficiary. The distribution shall be made as a lump-sum payment in cash, with the exception of the portion of an account invested in Employer Stock, with respect to which the Participant may elect a
distribution in kind. There shall be no installment form of distribution except as permitted by a retirement income manager program adopted by the Employer, or as provided under Section 9.6 with respect to required minimum distributions.</STRIKE>
Any distribution permitted or required under the Plan shall be made on a pro-rata basis <U>in cash</U> from all of the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts and investment funds, except: (1)&nbsp;a Participant may designate the portion of a
<STRIKE>partial</STRIKE> distribution<U>, other than an Installment Distribution,</U> to be made from the Participant&#146;s Roth Deferral Account or from all of his or her other accounts; (2)&nbsp;required minimum distributions shall be made from a
Participant&#146;s Roth Elective Deferral Account only after complete distribution from all other accounts<U>; (3)&nbsp;the Participant may elect a distribution in-kind of the portion of an account invested in Employer Stock; </U>and
(<U>4</U><STRIKE>3</STRIKE>)&nbsp;correction of excess Annual Additions shall be made in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.4. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 8 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 2 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DEATH DISTRIBUTION PROVISIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">If the Participant dies before <U>full</U> distribution of the
Participant&#146;s <U>entire</U> Nonforfeitable Account balance has been made, the Participant&#146;s Beneficiary may apply for a distribution of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance <U>in the same form as permitted under
Section&nbsp;9.3, subject to Section&nbsp;9.6(b)</U> <STRIKE>in a single sum</STRIKE>. Subject to Section<U> </U>_9.11(a), the Beneficiary may, instead, delay distribution until distribution is required under Section&nbsp;9.6(b). </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">DISTRIBUTION UNDER QUALIFIED DOMESTIC RELATIONS ORDER </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Distribution of all or a portion of a Participant&#146;s
Nonforfeitable Account balance will be made according to the terms of a &#147;qualified domestic relations order&#148; to the spouse, former spouse, child or other dependent of a Participant, even though the Participant is not otherwise eligible for
a distribution under the Plan. A qualified domestic relations order is a domestic relations order, judgment, or decree (including the approval of a property settlement agreement) that (a)&nbsp;relates to the provision of child support, alimony, or
property rights to a spouse, former spouse, child, or other dependent of a Participant and (b)&nbsp;is made pursuant to the domestic relations law of any state; provided that the Plan Administrator determines that such order meets the requirements
of Code Section&nbsp;414(p) and the Plan&#146;s Procedures for Processing Domestic Relations Orders (&#147;QDRO Procedures&#148;). Reasonable legal fees and expenses incurred in determining if an order is a qualified domestic relations order, shall
be charged to the account of the Participant and the account of the alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) seeking the determination, as provided in the QDRO Procedures. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">An alternate payee may apply for a distribution of the portion of the Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance that is payable to the alternate payee
pursuant to the qualified domestic relations order any time after the order is determined to be a qualified domestic relations order<U>, and in any of the forms permitted under Section&nbsp;9.3</U>. Subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(a), the alternate
payee may<STRIKE>,</STRIKE> instead<STRIKE>,</STRIKE> delay distribution<U> until the Participant&#146;s Required Beginning Date as determined under Section&nbsp;9.6(c).</U> <STRIKE>until the alternate payee attains age 65, at which time
distribution shall be made to the alternate payee.</STRIKE> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.10</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">AMOUNT AND TIMING OF DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The amount of a distribution to a Participant, Beneficiary, or alternate
payee shall not exceed the value of such individual&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance on the distribution date, reduced for outstanding loans, administrative expenses, and other appropriate amounts. Distribution shall be made <U>(or, in the case
of an Installment Distribution, shall begin) </U>within an administratively practicable period after the individual&#146;s application therefor (or the date benefits become distributable without the individual&#146;s consent) and after the Plan
Administrator receives all documents or information required to confirm the distribution is proper under the law and the terms of the Plan. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">9.11</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">NOTICE AND CONSENT TO DISTRIBUTION </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Small Benefit Distribution Without Consent</U>: If the value of a Participant&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance does not exceed $5,000 (determined without regard to the Participant&#146;s Employee Contribution
Account) and the Participant has severed employment with all Participating Employers, distribution shall be made to the Participant <U>in a single lump sum </U>without the Participant&#146;s consent, subject to Section&nbsp;9.11(d). Distribution
shall also be made to a Beneficiary or alternate payee <U>in a single lump sum </U>without that individual&#146;s consent if the value of that individual&#146;s Nonforfeitable Account balance does not exceed $5,000 (determined without regard to the
Employee Contribution Account). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt"><U>Participant and Alternate Payee Notice and Consent Requirements</U>: Distribution shall not be made to a Participant (or alternate payee) before
Normal Retirement Age without the Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) consent if the Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) Nonforfeitable Account Balance exceeds $5,000 (determined without regard to the Participant&#146;s (or
alternate payee&#146;s) Employee Contribution Account). No less than 30 days and no more than 180 days before the date of a distribution for which a Participant&#146;s (or alternate payee&#146;s) consent is required under this section, the Plan
Administrator shall provide the Participant (or alternate payee) with the notice </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 8 to </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 3 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">
described in Treasury Regulation &#167; 1.411(a)-11(c) or, in accordance with Treasury Regulations, a summary of that notice. In addition to describing a Participant&#146;s<U> (or alternate
payee&#146;s)</U> right (if any) to defer receipt of a distribution<U> and the material features of the optional forms of benefit available under the Plan</U>, such notice shall also describe the consequences of failing to defer receipt of a
distribution. Notwithstanding the above, distribution may be made less than 30 days after such notice or summary is given, provided that: (1)&nbsp;the Plan Administrator clearly informs the Participant (or alternate payee) that the Participant (or
alternate payee) has a right to a period of at least 30 days after receiving the notice or summary to consider the decision of whether or not to elect a distribution, and (2)&nbsp;the Participant (or alternate payee), after receiving the notice or
summary, affirmatively elects a distribution. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Rollover Notice</U>: No less than 30 days and no more than 180 days before the date of a distribution that is an eligible rollover distribution (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9), the Plan Administrator shall provide
the distributee (as defined in Section&nbsp;9.9) of such distribution with the notice described in Section&nbsp;402(f) of the Code or, in accordance with Treasury Regulations, a summary of that notice. Notwithstanding the above, distribution may be
made less than 30 days after such notice or summary is given, provided that: (1)&nbsp;the Plan Administrator clearly informs the distributee that the distributee has a right to a period of at least 30 days after receiving the notice or summary to
consider the decision of whether or not to elect a direct rollover, and (2)&nbsp;the distributee, after receiving the notice or summary, affirmatively elects a distribution. In the case of a series of installment payments that are eligible rollover
distributions, the rules of this subparagraph shall apply only to the first such installment payment, in accordance with Section&nbsp;402(f) of the Code and applicable Treasury Regulations. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Automatic Rollovers</U>: In the event of a mandatory distribution to a Participant greater than $1,000 from their Roth Elective Deferral Account, or from all other Plan Accounts (combined), in accordance with the
provisions of Section&nbsp;9.11(a), if the Participant does not elect to have such distribution paid directly to an eligible retirement plan specified by the Participant in a direct rollover or to receive the distribution directly, then the Plan
Administrator shall pay the distribution in a direct rollover to an individual retirement plan designated by the Plan Administrator. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>This Amendment 8 is effective February&nbsp;1, 2014. </I></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>COSTCO BENEFITS COMMITTEE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>RESOLUTION AMENDING RETIREMENT PLAN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Amendment No.&nbsp;9 to Plan Restated Effective January&nbsp;1, 2011 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Costco Benefits Committee (the &#147;Committee&#148;) is authorized by the Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) Sections 14.6 and
15.2 to amend the Plan; and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, the Committee wishes to make certain changes and clarifications to the Plan; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Plan is amended as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following changes and clarifications are made to Article 1: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B></B>1.67</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;<B>Salary Deferral Agreement</B>&#148; means a written agreement or enrollment form (or written confirmation of a voice enrollment) in which a Participant elects to have his or her Compensation reduced by a
specified amount in whole percentages, or elects not to have his or her Compensation reduced. Salary Deferral Agreement also means a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduced by 3% under &#147;Automatic
Enrollment&#148; as described below and a Participant&#146;s default election to have his or her Compensation reduction percentage increased under &#147;Automatic Increases&#148; as described below. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for
non-Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. A Participant may elect to reduce Compensation for Catch-Up Contributions not less than 1% or more than 50%&nbsp;per pay period. These limits apply to pre-tax
Contributions and Roth Elective Deferrals combined. The determination of whether a contribution is a Catch-Up Contribution is, however, determined in accordance with Section&nbsp;3.1(e) and Code Section&nbsp;414(v). Salary Deferral Agreements shall
be governed by the following:<B> </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>**** </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Automatic Increases</U>. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(i)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Except as provided in (ii)&nbsp;below, the Compensation reduction percentage in an Eligible Employee&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement shall be automatically increased by 1% on each anniversary of the Employee&#146;s
Employment Commencement Date (or re-employment date, if applicable), unless the Employee <STRIKE>suspends or </STRIKE>amends his or her Salary Deferral Agreement during the 30-day period ending on such anniversary date. Such increase is considered
an amendment to the Employee&#146;s Salary Deferral Agreement, and is effective on the first day of the pay period (or extended pay period as provided in Section (a)) ending after the Employee&#146;s anniversary date described above. This automatic
increase shall not apply if the Compensation reduction percentage in the Employee&#146;s then-existing Salary Deferral Agreement is either 0% or is 20% or more. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>**** </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.72</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;Spouse&#148; means the person who is treated as <STRIKE>a </STRIKE><U>the Participant&#146;s </U>spouse under federal law and who is legally married to the Participant <STRIKE>(as determined under the laws of the
state in which the Participant resides) </STRIKE>on the date distribution of benefits under the Plan commences or who was married to the Participant on the date of the Participant&#146;s death. However, a former spouse will be treated as the Spouse
to the extent provided under a qualified domestic relations order as described in Section&nbsp;414(p) of the Code.<U> For purposes of this definition, same-sex marriages and spouses are recognized in accordance with IRS Revenue Ruling 2013-17,
effective June&nbsp;26, 2013.</U> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 9 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 2 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following clarifications are made to Article 5: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">5.2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">ALLOCATION OF INVESTMENT INCOME (OR LOSS) AND ALLOCATION OF PLAN EXPENSES </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">All contributions to the Accounts of
each Participant in the Plan shall be reflected in units or shares of each Investment Fund and, in the case of the ESOP, in shares of Employer Stock, according to the investments elected by the Participant. As of each Valuation Date, the Plan
Administrator (or its agent, the third party recordkeeper) shall adjust accounts to reflect the net income, gains and losses since the last Valuation Date, and any administrative expenses charged to the Accounts, provided that gains, losses, and
other credits or charges will be separately allocated on a reasonable and consistent basis to each Participant&#146;s Roth Elective Deferral Account and the Participant&#146;s other accounts under the Plan. Dividends with respect to Employer Stock
shall be allocated and reinvested or paid as provided in Section&nbsp;7.5 hereof. The Plan Administrator may allocate the reasonable and necessary fees and expenses of administering the Plan to the Accounts of Participants and Beneficiaries, and it
may pay such fees and expenses from the Accounts <U>(on a pro-rata, per-capita or other reasonable basis) </U>to the extent they are not paid by the Employer<STRIKE>; provided such fees and expenses are incurred for the administration and operation
of the Plan and are not &#147;settlor&#148; expenses</STRIKE>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following clarifications are made to Article 7: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">7.3</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">OPTIONAL PASS-THROUGH VOTING OF NON-EMPLOYER STOCK </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Plan Administrator may direct the Trustee, from time to
time, to allow Participants to direct the Trustee as to the manner in which shares of the Investment Funds, other than Employer Stock, allocated to each Participant&#146;s Account shall be voted or how the Trustee should respond to a tender offer or
similar ownership right. If the Plan Administrator permits such pass-through voting, the Trustee shall deliver to each Participant <STRIKE>a copy of any proxy solicitation materials, tender offer, or other information given to shareholders of the
securities</STRIKE><U>the information the Plan is required to deliver under applicable law</U>, together with a <U>description of the procedure </U><STRIKE>form </STRIKE>by which the Participant may <STRIKE>instruct </STRIKE><U>give direction
on</U><STRIKE>the Trustee</STRIKE> how to vote or whether to tender the securities. The Trustee shall vote such securities through proxy in accordance with the instructions received from the Participant entitled to vote the securities and shall
tender or exercise other ownership rights in accordance with the instructions of the Participant. The Trustee shall not vote, tender, or otherwise exercise ownership rights for any such securities for which instructions are not received from the
Participant. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">7.4</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">PASS-THROUGH VOTING OF EMPLOYER STOCK </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><U>The following provisions apply with respect to Employer Stock held in
the ESOP portion of the Plan pursuant to Section&nbsp;7.5(a): </U> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Information and Procedures</U>. Participants who have investments in Employer Stock shall be provided with the same information as <STRIKE>that which </STRIKE>is provided to other shareholders<STRIKE>, including all
proxies and proxy solicitation material</STRIKE>, and the Participant shall have the right to direct the Trustee as to the voting, tender, and other similar rights of the Employer Stock allocated to the Participant&#146;s Account. Information
regarding a Participant&#146;s exercise of such rights shall be maintained in accordance with procedures designed to safeguard the confidentiality of the purchase, holding, or sale of Employer Stock and the exercise of voting, tender, and other
ownership rights, except to the extent necessary to comply with federal or state laws that are not preempted by ERISA (such as the reporting requirement for Insiders under Section&nbsp;16 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934). </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(c)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Voting of Employer Stock</U>. A Participant may direct the Trustee as to the manner in which Employer Stock allocated to the Participant&#146;s Account shall be voted. Before each meeting of the shareholders, the
Employer Stock Fiduciary or the Independent Fiduciary shall deliver or arrange for delivery to each Participant <STRIKE>a copy of any proxy solicitation materials</STRIKE><U>any information required under applicable law </U>together with a
<U>description of the procedure</U><STRIKE>form</STRIKE> by which the Participant may instruct the Trustee how to vote the Employer Stock. The Trustee shall vote Employer Stock through proxy in accordance with instructions received from the
Participant entitled to vote such Employer Stock. The Trustee shall not vote Employer Stock for which voting instructions are not received from Participants entitled to vote such Employer Stock. Neither the Trustee, the Employer Stock Fiduciary, nor
the Independent Fiduciary shall express any opinion, make any recommendation, or exert any undue influence with respect to Participants&#146; voting of Employer Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 9 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 3 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(d)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Tender Offers</U>. In the event of a tender offer for shares of Employer Stock, the Trustee shall sell, convey or transfer Employer Stock only in accordance with the <STRIKE>written </STRIKE>instructions of the
Participant. The Independent Fiduciary shall deliver or arrange for delivery to each Participant <STRIKE>all information provided to other shareholders, including </STRIKE>(a)&nbsp;<U>any information required under applicable law,</U><STRIKE> a copy
of the description of the terms and conditions of the tender offer filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission, (b)&nbsp;a copy of the statement from management setting forth its position with respect to the tender offer filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission, </STRIKE>(<STRIKE>c</STRIKE><U>b</U>) <STRIKE>an instruction form to be completed</STRIKE><U>a description of the procedure</U> by<U> which</U> a Participant <STRIKE>who wishes to</STRIKE><U>may</U> instruct the
Trustee to tender Employer Stock in response to the tender offer<U>,</U><STRIKE> and written instructions which</STRIKE><U> including a </U>state<U>ment</U> that Employer Stock allocated to the Participant will not be tendered if the <U>Participant
does not follow such procedure</U><STRIKE>instruction form is not returned to the Trustee</STRIKE> by the indicated deadline, and (<STRIKE>d</STRIKE><U>c</U>) such other <STRIKE>materials or </STRIKE>information as the Independent Fiduciary may deem
necessary or appropriate. The Trustee shall sell, convey, or transfer shares of Employer Stock pursuant to the terms of the tender offer as directed by the Participants<STRIKE> on the instruction forms</STRIKE>. Neither the Trustee, the Employer
Stock Fiduciary, nor the Independent Fiduciary shall express any opinion or recommendation, or exert any undue influence with respect to Participants&#146; exercise of their rights under the tender offer. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">7.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">INVESTMENT IN EMPLOYER STOCK </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Participants may direct investment of their Accounts into Employer Stock. In addition, if the Employer so elects, it may make Matching Contributions, Company Contributions, and Discretionary Contributions in Employer
Stock, or if made in cash, it may direct the Trustee to purchase Employer Stock with such cash contributions prior to the allocation of Employer contributions to Accounts. The portion of this Plan which is invested in Employer Stock <U>pursuant to
this Section&nbsp;7.5(a) </U>is hereby designated as an ESOP and a stock bonus plan, and it is designed to invest exclusively in Qualifying Employer Securities. The Plan Administrator may not divest the ESOP of Employer Stock. Up to 100% of the
assets of Accounts may be invested in Employer Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Employer Stock <U>held in the Plan pursuant to Section&nbsp;7.5(a) </U>shall be held in one or more ESOP funds established by the Plan Administrator and maintained by the Trustee. <STRIKE>Assets of Accounts invested in
Employer Stock at the direction of Participants shall be held in such ESOP fund or funds.</STRIKE> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">* * * * </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following changes are made to Article 10: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.1</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOAN PROGRAM </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A Participant may borrow limited amounts from the Participant&#146;s Salary Deferral Account
(excluding his or her Roth Elective Deferral Account), <STRIKE>Matching Contribution Account (to the extent vested), </STRIKE>Profit Sharing Contribution Account, any Nondeductible Voluntary Contribution Account established under a Prior Plan, and
any Rollover Account established under Section&nbsp;6.1 (referred to collectively in this Article as &#147;eligible accounts&#148;). Participant loans shall not be made from a Participant&#146;s Company or Discretionary Contribution Accounts,
<U>Matching Contribution Account, </U>ESOP Dividend Reinvestment Account, Rescission Account, Qualified Non-Elective Contribution Account, <U>or </U>Roth Elective Deferral Account<STRIKE>, or from the non-vested portion of the Participant&#146;s
Matching Contribution Account</STRIKE>. Participant loans are made only in the form of a lump sum. Only one loan from the plan may be outstanding at any time, and outstanding loans may not be amended or refinanced. Moreover, a Participant who has an
outstanding loan from any other plan of a Participating Employer is not eligible for a loan from this Plan until the loan to the other plan is repaid in full. In the event of default on a plan loan, a Participant may not apply for another loan
earlier than six months after the defaulted loan is repaid in full. </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Amendment No. 9 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Costco 401(k) Retirement Plan Restated Effective January 1, 2011 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Page 4 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee may make a loan to a Participant from the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts, in accordance
with the terms of this Article and any written loan policy, upon the application of a Participant who is in Eligible Employment and who meets objective criteria established in loan documents to ensure that the loan will be repaid according to its
terms. The loan program shall be administered in a uniform and nondiscriminatory manner in accordance with established rules and procedures, which may be changed from time to time. The Plan Administrator may establish a written loan policy separate
from this document, and any such policy, as amended from time to time, is incorporated herein by this reference. Loans shall be made on a reasonably equivalent basis and shall be available without regard to a Participant&#146;s race, color,
religion, gender, age, or national origin. Furthermore, loans shall not be made available to Highly Compensated Employees in an amount greater than the amount made available to other Participants. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">10.5</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">LOAN <STRIKE>ORIGINATION </STRIKE>FEE<U>S</U> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Trustee may charge a reasonable loan origination fee<U> and
a reasonable annual loan maintenance fee</U><STRIKE>, which shall be deducted from the Participant&#146;s eligible accounts at the time the loan is made</STRIKE>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>The following clarification is made to Article 13: </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">13.7</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">COMMUNICATIONS </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Written communications to the Plan Administrator, the Plan, a Participating Employer, the
Trustee, the Committee or other fiduciaries, or their agents or representatives, must be received before the expiration of any time period expressed herein or in related documents (including the summary plan description and policies and procedures
for this Plan). To the extent the Plan Administrator, the Trustee, a Participating Employer or the Plan approves the use of electronic or telephonic communications to or from Plan Participants (as permitted by the Code<U>,</U><STRIKE> or
</STRIKE>the Act, <STRIKE>as</STRIKE><U>or other</U> applicable<U> law</U>), and to the extent not otherwise prohibited or provided otherwise hereunder, such electronic or telephonic communications are treated as written communications hereunder.
The Plan Administrator&#146;s (or the Plan&#146;s, a Participating Employer&#146;s, the Trustee&#146;s, the Committee&#146;s or other fiduciaries&#146;, as applicable), or their agents&#146; or representatives&#146; records will be conclusive as to
whether a communication has been sent or received and the date of such sending or receipt, unless the sender produces a United States Postal Service return receipt. The common law &#147;mailbox rule&#148; shall not apply to determine receipt or the
date of receipt by the Plan Administrator (or the Plan, a Participating Employer, the Trustee, the Committee or other fiduciaries, as applicable), or their agents or representatives. The common law mailbox rule shall apply for all other purposes
under the Plan. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Effective Dates: </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
